Date: Tue, 01 Dec 1998 09:11:26 +0100
From: verhaegs@imec.be (Staf Verhaegen)
Subject: Re: Old ideas - assembly ?

Maxim Olivier-Adlhoch wrote:
>
> One of the reaons E compiles so fast is because its written 100% in
> assembly.  Thus making a new E compiler will Certainly be slower in
> compilation time.
>

Actually the compiler is so fast because E is a typeless language. The
compiler
doesn't have to check if arguments to functions or operators have the right
type, if an implicit conversion is necessary or not, etc.
A compiler written in C with FLEX and YACC and a good optimising compiler
will
not be that much slower. Of course you will have to optimise your C code
than.

greets,
