Ok.
I have never used BlizBasic but as the same suggest it is a Basic 8). E is
a way lot more powerful than a Basic language. It can be described as a
cross between a (limited but simpler) C++ and Assembler implementation. It
has OOP, exception handling, very easy use of pointers, simple syntax,
support for inline Assembly, OS friendly interface (it uses all the
standard OS libraries with no problems).

However it cannot provide anything much that that OS cannot. Gadtools is
very limited (but surely it supports colors), maybe you should have a look
at BOOPSI. The ultra inflated use of MUI and such sort of bloated GUI just
for simple tools is not a good thing. Whatever MUI fans may say, MUI is
slow and uses tons of memeory even though more tasks share the same
libraries. Just have a look at web and Voyager to see which is faster and
"more" efficient when talking about resource handling. Using MUI just to
have 2 scaleable buttons in a window is not a very good thing, as people
tend too look at their resource when using a program, and if another
program can do the same things, but it smaller, faster and uses less
memory (evn though it can resize its window) I think they probably will go
and use this one.

Enough said about MUI.

However, E comes with a quite good "framework" for GUIs, by using a
relative small modoule (~40K) that is able to create scaleable GUIs with
many different gadgets (and new ones can be easily created if you need
them). It may be worth a look.

Have fun.

M&F

