>For example my WB colour 2 is white and should return 255, 255, 255
>but instead GetRGB4 returns 15, 15, 15. For the same example the
>attactprogram returns -1, -1, -1.

GetRGB4() is named as it iss because it is 4 bit. 4 bits = 0 - 15. It
returns
the numbers it is supposed to.

Your attached program also returns the correct values, at least for me. Try
printing them in hex instead and it will be much easier to see.

GetRGB32() ofcourse is 32 bit, and therefore returns 0 - 2^32-1, wich means
that \d, wich prints signed numbers, will print -1 for the largest,
something
very large negative for middle, and still zero for zero.
Shr( table[ x ] , 24 ) will give you the desired 0-255 number.

