>         I am just wondering how i can create an executable file from e ? i
>know that the header starts with $000003F3 but that's about it.

>I know this is a big big ask but thanks for any help and/or examples you
can
>give to me

Well, if we are to keep it simple this is how the simplest executable file
looks: (Must be position independant)
All numbers are LONGs:
$3f3 $0 $1 $0 $0
LONGs of code. That's codesize/4, rounded up.
$3e9
LONGs of code, again.
Now you write the actual code, pad so it really is dividable by 4.
$3f2
EOF

That's about as much as you need to know if you just want to write a
*really*
simple exefile.

