Just wanted to but in and say that in the RKRMs 'libraries' book they talk
about using layers.library under intuition and it is expressly stated that
one
should NOT assume any window or Screen structure to be safe with
layers.library functions...  the system is using them and dangerous race
conditions and other nasties can occur if you are not carefull...

generally, if you are going to intuition, do not go beyond graphics.library
and rastports.  you CAN use bitmaps directly though.  I would recommend you
use a non-smart-refresj window if you do not want to use too much memory, as
it does not allocate any bitmap memory when opening... it only stores the
window struct data itself (But you must refresh everytime a window is
moved/sized layer over-off of your window!).

I think, only the various layer to front and similar functions are
considered
safe.

I have implemented many pop-up gadgets for easygui and I find the fastest
and
easiest solution is always to open such a borderless window (or even a
requester if you are familiar with them...) and draw using any
graphics.library routines directly on that.  its the only system-legal way
of
doing it.  (plus, using windows (under Amiga) is not memory intensive).
anyways...)

